text:
Lazav probably shouldn't get the unblockability in addition to the changing effect. It's a little too easy if it enables itself. Plus, the trigger is wonky in the event of multiple combat steps. And it reads weird if you want to keep it the same copy. I'd format it a little bit more like Steel Hellkite.

 ex:
1U: Lazav can't be blocked this turn.
B: If Lazav dealt damage to an opponent this turn, it becomes a copy of target creature in that player's graveyard, except its name is still Lazav, it's legendary in addition to other types, it has this ability, and it has "1U: Lazav can't be blocked this turn."

3/2 seems too powerful for a shapeshifter at 3 mana, too. I can imagine folks using it just to get the unblockable beats in. I'd personally want to lose the unblockable pieces altogether, but you did put 'evasive' in the title. Point is, if he's going to shapeshift, he should have a body that encourages you to change form.


I like the idea of the slime a lot, but would probably make the abilities more distinct. On ETB, destroy artifact or enchantment. Sac, destroy just artifact. Exile, destroy enchantment. And/or restrict the other two abilities to sorc speed only. As is, I worry it's a bit obnoxiously potent. Not OP, but versatile enough to feel overbearing.

Nitpicks aside I like the ideas.
